contract_type.raw_snippet: Outsourcing Contract on Development of Miaoli Royal Resort Hotel
contract_type.reasoning: The agreement's title and the substance (Party B providing planning, design, environmental assessment, construction monitoring and related professional services to Party A) indicate an outsourcing of development-related professional services. This fits the 'Outsourcing Agreement' category.

agreement_date.reasoning: The date appears in the contract header and the signature block (immediately after the parties block), indicating when the contract was executed/signed.

effective_date.reasoning: The contract does not contain an explicit "effective as of" or "commencement" clause. A signing date is present, but no language stating the agreement 'takes effect' on that date is provided, so no explicit effective date can be extracted.

expiration_date.reasoning: The contract contains planned task durations (Article VII) but does not state an overall contract term, fixed end date, or 'perpetual' language. Therefore there is no explicit expiration/term to extract.

governing_law.raw_snippet:
II. Should either Party herein initiate a legal proceeding for revoking any arbitration result regarding the Contract, both Parties
herein agree to take the Miaoli District Court of Taiwan as the competent court of first instance pursuant to the laws of the
R.O.C..
governing_law.reasoning: Article XI ties dispute resolution to arbitration in Miaoli County and specifies that court proceedings (to revoke arbitration) will be in the Miaoli District Court "pursuant to the laws of the R.O.C.", which identifies the governing legal system as the laws of the Republic of China (Taiwan).

notice_period.reasoning: The contract does not contain any clause about automatic renewal nor any advance notice period required to prevent renewal. Therefore no notice-to-prevent-renewal period is present.

renewal_term.reasoning: There is no renewal or automatic extension clause in the agreement to extract a renewal term from.
